From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0034/N] Modules.gmk: java.base borrows macosx/classes on bsd target

Java class compilation for `bsd` target fails with hundreds of
"cannot find symbol" errors because OpenJDK's tree has no
`src/java.base/bsd/classes/` directory -- the BSD-derived NIO
providers (`BsdFileSystemProvider`, `KQueueSelectorProvider`,
`DefaultFileSystemProvider`, etc.) live under
`src/java.base/macosx/classes/`.

Two-part fix:

1. Override `FindModuleSrcDirs` to include `macosx/classes` only
   when the module is `java.base`. java.desktop's macosx/classes
   is Cocoa-only and must not be pulled in.

2. Override `GetModuleSrcPath` to add `*/macosx/classes` to javac's
   `--module-source-path`. javac uses this wildcard pattern to
   resolve which module a file belongs to. Without it, files under
   `macosx/classes/` produce "not in a module on the module source
   path" errors -- even when javac is given them via SRC, it can't
   match the module name from the path components.

A real `bsd/classes` directory split is a Phase 2 cleanup.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md (patch 0034)

--- a/make/common/Modules.gmk
+++ b/make/common/Modules.gmk
@@ -315,3 +315,27 @@ endef
 ################################################################################
 
 endif # _MODULES_GMK
+
+
+# Phase 1: when targeting bsd (CheriBSD), the upstream tree has no bsd/classes
+# directory. java.base needs macosx/classes for BSD-derived NIO providers
+# (BsdFileSystemProvider, KQueueSelectorProvider). java.desktop's macosx/classes
+# is Cocoa-only and must NOT be pulled in. Override FindModuleSrcDirs to add
+# macosx/classes only when $1 is java.base, and extend GetModuleSrcPath so
+# javac's --module-source-path includes macosx/classes (needed for javac to
+# resolve module of files under that root -- even if only java.base actually
+# compiles files from it).
+ifeq ($(OPENJDK_TARGET_OS), bsd)
+FindModuleSrcDirs = \
+    $(strip $(wildcard \
+        $(addsuffix /$(strip $1), $(GENERATED_SRC_DIRS) $(IMPORT_MODULES_SRC)) \
+        $(foreach sub, $(SRC_SUBDIRS), $(addsuffix /$(strip $1)/$(sub), $(TOP_SRC_DIRS))) \
+        $(if $(filter java.base,$(strip $1)), \
+            $(foreach top, $(TOP_SRC_DIRS), $(top)/$(strip $1)/macosx/classes))))
+
+GetModuleSrcPath = \
+    $(call PathList, \
+        $(addsuffix /*, $(GENERATED_SRC_DIRS) $(IMPORT_MODULES_SRC)) \
+        $(foreach sub, $(SRC_SUBDIRS) macosx/classes, \
+            $(addsuffix /*/$(sub), $(TOP_SRC_DIRS))))
+endif
